{"language": "kotlin", "mode": "NEP", "expected_edit_kind": "Inline", "label": "Kotlin NEP: extend lambda after adding parameter", "file_path": "Filter.kt", "cursor_line": 1, "original_content": "val items = listOf(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)\nval even = items.filter { it % 2 == 0 }", "current_content": "val items = listOf(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)\nval even = items.filter { it % 2 == 0 }.map {", "prompt": "<|file_sep|>Filter.kt.diff\noriginal:\nval even = items.filter { it % 2 == 0 }\nupdated:\nval even = items.filter { it % 2 == 0 }.map {\n<|file_sep|>original/Filter.kt\nval items = listOf(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)\nval even = items.filter { it % 2 == 0 }\n<|file_sep|>current/Filter.kt\nval items = listOf(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)\nval even = items.filter { it % 2 == 0 }.map {\n<|file_sep|>updated/Filter.kt", "response": "\nval items = listOf(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)\nval even = items.filter { it % 2 == 0 }.map {\n    it * 2\n}\n", "error": null, "elapsed_seconds": 0.3}
