{"language": "rust", "mode": "NEP", "expected_edit_kind": "Inline", "label": "Rust NEP: rename struct field propagates to constructor and access", "file_path": "point.rs", "cursor_line": 2, "original_content": "struct Point {\n    x: f64,\n    y: f64,\n}\n\nfn new_point() -> Point {\n    Point { x: 0.0, y: 0.0 }\n}\n\nfn print_point(p: &Point) {\n    println!(\"({}, {})\", p.x, p.y);\n}", "current_content": "struct Point {\n    x: f64,\n    z: f64,\n}\n\nfn new_point() -> Point {\n    Point { x: 0.0, y: 0.0 }\n}\n\nfn print_point(p: &Point) {\n    println!(\"({}, {})\", p.x, p.y);\n}", "prompt": "<|file_sep|>point.rs.diff\noriginal:\n    y: f64,\nupdated:\n    z: f64,\n<|file_sep|>original/point.rs\nstruct Point {\n    x: f64,\n    y: f64,\n}\n\nfn new_point() -> Point {\n    Point { x: 0.0, y: 0.0 }\n}\n\nfn print_point(p: &Point) {\n    println!(\"({}, {})\", p.x, p.y);\n}\n<|file_sep|>current/point.rs\nstruct Point {\n    x: f64,\n    z: f64,\n}\n\nfn new_point() -> Point {\n    Point { x: 0.0, y: 0.0 }\n}\n\nfn print_point(p: &Point) {\n    println!(\"({}, {})\", p.x, p.y);\n}\n<|file_sep|>updated/point.rs", "response": "\nstruct Point {\n    x: f64,\n    y: f64,\n    z: f64,\n}\n\nfn new_point() -> Point {\n    Point { x: 0.0, y: 0.0, z: 0.0 }\n}\n\nfn print_point(p: &Point) {\n    println!(\"({}, {}, {})\", p.x, p.y, p.z);\n}\n", "error": null, "elapsed_seconds": 0.581}
{"language": "rust", "mode": "NEP", "expected_edit_kind": "Inline", "label": "Rust NEP: change return type propagates to function body", "file_path": "parse_num.rs", "cursor_line": 0, "original_content": "fn parse_num(s: &str) -> i32 {\n    s.parse().unwrap()\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let n: i32 = parse_num(\"42\");\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}", "current_content": "fn parse_num(s: &str) -> Result<i32, std::num::ParseIntError> {\n    s.parse().unwrap()\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let n: i32 = parse_num(\"42\");\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}", "prompt": "<|file_sep|>parse_num.rs.diff\noriginal:\nfn parse_num(s: &str) -> i32 {\nupdated:\nfn parse_num(s: &str) -> Result<i32, std::num::ParseIntError> {\n<|file_sep|>original/parse_num.rs\nfn parse_num(s: &str) -> i32 {\n    s.parse().unwrap()\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let n: i32 = parse_num(\"42\");\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}\n<|file_sep|>current/parse_num.rs\nfn parse_num(s: &str) -> Result<i32, std::num::ParseIntError> {\n    s.parse().unwrap()\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let n: i32 = parse_num(\"42\");\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}\n<|file_sep|>updated/parse_num.rs", "response": "\nuse std::num::ParseIntError;\n\nfn parse_num(s: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> {\n    s.parse()\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let n: i32 = parse_num(\"42\")?;\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}\n", "error": null, "elapsed_seconds": 0.423}
