{"language": "rust", "mode": "NEP", "expected_edit_kind": "Suppress", "label": "Rust NEP: no change after converting to turbofish syntax", "file_path": "turbofish.rs", "cursor_line": 1, "original_content": "fn main() {\n    let n = \"42\".parse().unwrap();\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}", "current_content": "fn main() {\n    let n = \"42\".parse::<i32>().unwrap();\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}", "prompt": "<|file_sep|>turbofish.rs.diff\noriginal:\n    let n = \"42\".parse().unwrap();\nupdated:\n    let n = \"42\".parse::<i32>().unwrap();\n<|file_sep|>original/turbofish.rs\nfn main() {\n    let n = \"42\".parse().unwrap();\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}\n<|file_sep|>current/turbofish.rs\nfn main() {\n    let n = \"42\".parse::<i32>().unwrap();\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}\n<|file_sep|>updated/turbofish.rs", "response": "\nfn main() {\n    let n = \"42\".parse::<i32>().unwrap();\n    println!(\"{}\", n);\n}\n", "error": null, "elapsed_seconds": 0.204}
{"language": "rust", "mode": "NEP", "expected_edit_kind": "Inline+Jump", "label": "Rust NEP mixed: make function generic propagates to body and callers", "file_path": "generic.rs", "cursor_line": 0, "original_content": "fn first(items: &[i32]) -> i32 {\n    items[0]\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let nums = vec![1, 2, 3];\n    let f: i32 = first(&nums);\n    println!(\"{}\", f);\n}", "current_content": "fn first<T: Copy>(items: &[T]) -> T {\n    items[0]\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let nums = vec![1, 2, 3];\n    let f: i32 = first(&nums);\n    println!(\"{}\", f);\n}", "prompt": "<|file_sep|>generic.rs.diff\noriginal:\nfn first(items: &[i32]) -> i32 {\nupdated:\nfn first<T: Copy>(items: &[T]) -> T {\n<|file_sep|>original/generic.rs\nfn first(items: &[i32]) -> i32 {\n    items[0]\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let nums = vec![1, 2, 3];\n    let f: i32 = first(&nums);\n    println!(\"{}\", f);\n}\n<|file_sep|>current/generic.rs\nfn first<T: Copy>(items: &[T]) -> T {\n    items[0]\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let nums = vec![1, 2, 3];\n    let f: i32 = first(&nums);\n    println!(\"{}\", f);\n}\n<|file_sep|>updated/generic.rs", "response": "\nfn first<T: Copy>(items: &[T]) -> T {\n    items[0]\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let nums = vec![1, 2, 3];\n    let f: i32 = first(&nums);\n    println!(\"{}\", f);\n}\n", "error": null, "elapsed_seconds": 0.435}
{"language": "rust", "mode": "NEP", "expected_edit_kind": "Inline+Jump", "label": "Rust NEP mixed: add lifetime annotation propagates to struct and impl", "file_path": "lifetime.rs", "cursor_line": 0, "original_content": "struct Parser {\n    input: &str,\n}\n\nimpl Parser {\n    fn new(input: &str) -> Parser {\n        Parser { input }\n    }\n\n    fn peek(&self) -> char {\n        self.input.chars().next().unwrap()\n    }\n}", "current_content": "struct Parser<'a> {\n    input: &str,\n}\n\nimpl Parser {\n    fn new(input: &str) -> Parser {\n        Parser { input }\n    }\n\n    fn peek(&self) -> char {\n        self.input.chars().next().unwrap()\n    }\n}", "prompt": "<|file_sep|>lifetime.rs.diff\noriginal:\nstruct Parser {\nupdated:\nstruct Parser<'a> {\n<|file_sep|>original/lifetime.rs\nstruct Parser {\n    input: &str,\n}\n\nimpl Parser {\n    fn new(input: &str) -> Parser {\n        Parser { input }\n    }\n\n    fn peek(&self) -> char {\n        self.input.chars().next().unwrap()\n    }\n}\n<|file_sep|>current/lifetime.rs\nstruct Parser<'a> {\n    input: &str,\n}\n\nimpl Parser {\n    fn new(input: &str) -> Parser {\n        Parser { input }\n    }\n\n    fn peek(&self) -> char {\n        self.input.chars().next().unwrap()\n    }\n}\n<|file_sep|>updated/lifetime.rs", "response": "\nstruct Parser<'a> {\n    input: &'a str,\n}\n\nimpl<'a> Parser<'a> {\n    fn new(input: &'a str) -> Parser<'a> {\n        Parser { input }\n    }\n\n    fn peek(&self) -> char {\n        self.input.chars().next().unwrap()\n    }\n}\n", "error": null, "elapsed_seconds": 0.476}
